texts.text: >As you sit in the Hideout,
>Seiran and Jeng Yun perform some sort of strange dance...
And move my right hand forward... Like this...?
Very good! Now, shift your weight also to the right...
What are you doing?
Is this dance practice?

Oh, you don't know?
This is tai chi.
No, this is called tai chi.
I'm guessing you thought we only knew kung fu.
Tai chi is a martial art that revolves around training your mind and spirit.
You told me the same thing a second ago...
Why are y'all doin' it now all the sudden?
It's been nice and sunny out lately, right?
So I decided to invite Jeng Yun,
and join a tai chi group that spends the morning practicing in the park.
Yes. It feels so good to do tai chi in the morning.
Oh, very good! Your last move had a nice flow to it!
I think I'm starting to get the hang of it!
Then let me add one more little tidbit.
Most moves in tai chi look very slow, but they can be deadly with some added force.
And Jeng Yun, you may do nicely for a quick test.
Mind if I try it out on you?
Yes, please do!
Here it goes... Hah!
>Seiran takes a stab at Jeng Yun with her hand!
Hmph!
Oh, you absorbed it completely. Well done, Jeng Yun.
Thank you. I have been training after all!
Yes, true... Then how about this!
Hah...!
>Seiran attempts a palm strike on Jeng Yun's gut!
Guh?!
H-How do I describe this...? I felt it throughout my body...
That was a palm strike. But it's no ordinary palm strike.
It can really mess up your insides.
I held back just now, but that's what it's designed to do.
My insides...? I see...
It doesn't matter how strong your opponent may be.
No amount of training will make your internal organs stronger.
I never knew such a technique existed. It's very interesting!
Would you mind teaching me it?
My pleasure! How about you, [sys user_name]?
You don't need muscles to learn how to do this.
Sure.
No thanks.
Great! I'm happy to see that you're so enthusiastic about this!
First, try copying what I do. Start by standing like this...
Oh, don't be such a party pooper...!
I'll work with you hand in hand, okayâ™¡
>She contorts your body into a tai chi stance...
You two are doing great. Just needs a little more polish.
Thank you very much!
But remember, it's dangerous so don't use it on anyone, alright?
I get Jeng Yun, but you too, Newbie?
Wait... Crap!
It's time for the weather forecast! Where's the remote?!
>Ririn turns on the TV and you see a weather reporter in the city.
Good morning!
This is Saara Mizuno, here to bring you today's forecast!
We're looking at sunny skies again today across the country.
We're even looking at a record sunny period for the spring.

*Swoon*
Saara looks as pretty as ever...
Who?
Saara?
Yo, she's the one that just started appearin' on TV,
and became super popular by bein' the weather girl... Er, reporter...!
Are you a fan of hers, Ririn?
I'm a huge fan! I mean, look at her! She's gorgeous!
She has a great personality too! I heard she treats all her fans really well!
You heard? So you've never seen or met her before...?
I tried once when she was out reporting, but she had a huge mob following her...
Security limited how many could stay too, so I didn't get to see her...

*Sigh*
Still, I want to see her in the flesh...
And find out what she smells like...
I know! You can make a video with her, Megakin!
That way, I'll finally be able to meet her,
and you'd get more views than usual! Two birds with one stone!
Say what? Make a video with her...? Doin' what exactly?
Hmm...
Like trying to predict the weather or something?
Yeah, you make it sound so easy...
This lack of rain is also expected to affect crop harvests for the year.
Oh, vegetable prices going up would be a problem.
Wait, really? Yeah, that would kinda suck...
I can't go back to living off sprouts! Saara, make it rain for us!

*Chuckle*
You know she's a reporter and not a shaman, right?
No, Saara, save us...
>A few days later.
Hah! Yah!
Hmph! Yah!
Phew. You've gotten quite good.
All thanks to you, Seiran.
You guys are really into this tai chi stuff, huh?
Even you, Newbie...
Yo, I guess they're havin' fun.
Anyways, it's time to get my daily fill of Saara now!
And this one's in her own rut...
>Ririn turns on the TV to a view of the city.
Good morning! This is Saara Mizuno, reporting in on the weather!
It looks like a sunny day again for the whole country.
And that concludes our weather forecast.
Unfortunately, this lack of rain has led to dammed reservoirs losing quite a bit of water.
Reports of water shortages have even started coming in.
The government has even begun considering the rationing of water.
Everyone, I deeply encourage you to start cutting back on your own water usage.
My family already does, so we're all set!
Yo, reservoirs are losin' water...?
Nice, [sys user_name]! That looked really good just now!

*Snicker*
But they're as happy as hens...
I'm sure it'll start rainin' again soon, but it might be good to ask everyone to cut back a little.
>A few more days later.
Good morning!
It's another sunny day again nationwide.
With regards to the water rationing that began last week...
Today, daytime water usage will become restricted in addition to the existing nighttime cuts.
The current drought has left our reservoirs with little water,
and are on the verge of running dry.
Experts are saying that such conditions are unprecedented.
Please, everyone, use your water wisely. I beg you.
Yo, I'm back.
How'd it go?!
No good. No water, nothin'. Not even regular drinks and stuff.
Damn...
It's not just water either. Other necessities are running dry too.
Yo, factories ain't gettin' any water because of this.
And panic buying has left the shelves barren.
What are we supposed to do...?
This is way worse than what we usually have to live with too...
Yo, we've managed so far,
but the hospitals ain't really functionin' without the water they need.
Nurses on social media are sayin' all this stuff online.
Like losin' patients that could've easily been saved...
I saw that video too...
I feel bad for that person,
but I feel worse for the nurses that had to watch it happen...
I even started getting that sinking feeling...
But answer me this. How long has it been since it last rained?
Has the dam ever dried up like this in the past...?
I mean, rationing only began a few days ago, but we're already at this point?
Yeah, it's happenin' way too fast.
What are you saying? A demon or something is behind this...?
Yo, I already looked into that.
But I ran into dead ends there too.
Excuse me.
Are you the demon users that I heard about?

Huh? No way...
Is that...?
Saara?!
